class 6
 alerts
 Alert is a pop up message. Alert takes complete focus from the webpage we are working.
 We cannot proceed further without handling an alert

 3 types of alerts
 1.web based / html alerts - we can simply inspect and perform action
 2. Javascript alert/ browser alerts - we can handle it by using switchTo() method
 3. windows based alerts - we cannot handle with selenium

 type of JS Alerts
 1.simple alert  - click on
 2. confirmation alert - either cancel or click ok
 3. prompt alert



 Frames
 frame is a seperate and independant window in a webpage. Frames allow developers to present multiple
 views in one webpage

 To handle JS alert we only have 4 methods available:
 1. accept()
 2. dismiss()
 3. getText()
 4. sendKeys()

 Frames
 Frame is a seperate and independent window in a webpage. Frames allow developers to present
 multiple views in one webpage

 3 ways to interact with frames:
 1. by index
 2. by name or id
 3. by webelement

 in alerts - switch manually and it switches back automatically
 in frames - switch manually and switch back manually


